\section*{Solution}

\subsection*{(a) Spring Constant}

The period \( T \) of a mass-spring system in SHM is given by the formula:
\[
T = 2\pi \sqrt{\frac{m}{k}}
\]
where \( m = 4 \, \text{kg} \) is the mass and \( k \) is the spring constant. Rearranging the formula to solve for \( k \), we have:
\[
