where $x$ is the displacement of the spring from its equilibrium position.

The torque $\tau$ on the pulley is then:

\begin{equation}
    \tau = rF = -krx.
\end{equation}

According to Newton's second law for rotation, the torque is also related to the angular acceleration $\alpha$ by:

\begin{equation}
    \tau = I\alpha.
\end{equation}

For small oscillations, the angular displacement $\theta$ is related to the linear displacement $x$ by $x = r\theta$. Thus, the angular acceleration $\alpha$ is:

\begin{equation}
